Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.92,0:00:07.02,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,It appeared as though humanity \Nwould be destroyed by the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.17,0:00:15.43,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But a single mage saved them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.56,0:00:27.73,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,He was called the Wizard King,\Nand he became a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.36,0:00:33.74,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,When he was younger, \NYami was on a journey to train,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.74,0:00:37.65,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,when the head of a little village asked him \Nto protect it some magical bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.65,0:00:39.37,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,He ended up battling the bandits,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.87,0:00:41.66,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,and during that battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.66,0:00:43.62,flashback,William,0000,0000,0000,,Yami, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.02,0:00:45.54,flashback,William,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you to watch my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.26,0:00:50.84,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Yami encountered Vangeance,\Nwho was nearby on another mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.84,0:00:53.95,flashback,William,0000,0000,0000,,First, I'm going to become a \NMagic Knights Squad captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.43,0:00:57.67,flashback,William,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the challenge is on. \NLet's see who can do it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.87,0:01:02.18,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,And all kinds of stuff happened after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.56,0:01:06.27,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,A few years later, \NJulius became the Wizard King,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:08.76,top,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,and both the golden weird mask guy and I
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.46,0:01:10.56,sign_6730_49_Captain_of_the_A,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(502,1)}The Wizard King's Attendant\N{\fs30}Marx Francois
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.76,0:01:13.01,top,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,were appointed Vice Captains\N of the Gray Deer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.56,0:01:13.82,sign_1785_19_Vice_Captain_of_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Vice Captain of the Gray Deer\N{\fs26}William Vangeance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.56,0:01:13.82,sign_1785_20_Vice_Captain_of_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Vice Captain of the Gray Deer\N{\fs26}Yami Sukehiro
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.01,0:01:14.72,top,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Then, one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.21,0:01:19.57,sign_6730_49_Captain_of_the_A,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(967,1)}28th Wizard King\N{\fs30}Julius Novachrono
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.91,0:01:18.44,top,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.44,0:01:19.57,top,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.91,0:01:22.29,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to be so formal with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.29,0:01:23.83,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.33,0:01:29.34,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you did amazing work exploring \Nthat dungeon the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:31.08,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,It was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.08,0:01:34.30,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you saved all the \Nknights who were caught
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.30,0:01:36.16,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,by the trap spell with your magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.16,0:01:38.86,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could've seen that magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.86,0:01:43.43,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'll give you the stars for \Nthat next time. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.43,0:01:46.29,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honored. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.53,0:01:52.81,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you were absolutely fierce in \Nthe defensive battle at Kuka Village.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.23,0:01:58.32,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you split the giant soldier that the \Nenemy created using rock magic in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.32,0:01:59.40,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that was nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.92,0:02:03.73,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it was everything! \NYou're going to give me some stars, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.73,0:02:07.81,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! I'm sure your \Ncaptain is very proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.81,0:02:09.96,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, it's about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.96,0:02:15.87,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. Sorry to have you \Nstop by when you're so busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.69,0:02:20.55,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,There's a job that I'd like \Nyou two to take on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.43,0:02:24.68,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Bandits?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.68,0:02:28.08,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they're causing trouble all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:30.18,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Would you two catch them for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.18,0:02:31.78,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.78,0:02:36.14,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Knights live to serve and \Nprotect the people of the Clover Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.14,0:02:38.93,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,We will happily accept this mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.93,0:02:39.73,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.73,0:02:41.70,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you just asking the two of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.05,0:02:44.61,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's possible that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.61,0:02:48.12,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,someone from the Magic Knights \Nis aiding the bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.12,0:02:50.25,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Well, can't say I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.40,0:02:54.27,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think they're ordinary bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.27,0:02:59.02,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,They're very organized and even \Nhave some ancient magic items.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.02,0:03:02.30,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty powerful ones, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.62,0:03:04.77,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,It may be that someone is providing them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.77,0:03:06.80,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,with magic items that we found in dungeons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.80,0:03:10.49,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's why you want us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.49,0:03:13.91,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,If all the Magic Knights were assigned \Nto this, evidence may be destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.91,0:03:15.93,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,and the guilty party may disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.93,0:03:18.31,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we've been assigned \Nto this secret mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.31,0:03:19.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.61,0:03:26.33,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Julius. What are you going to \Ndo if one of us is that traitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.33,0:03:28.83,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,We might just let the bandits escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.18,0:03:31.55,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that would be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.55,0:03:35.63,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,But I think I know you \Ntwo pretty well by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.63,0:03:38.84,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I've known you both since before \Nyou even joined the Magic Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.24,0:03:41.35,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:45.44,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,But if you two end up betraying me, \NI guess there's not much I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:48.22,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You always were a cunning old dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.56,0:03:50.55,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be counting on both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.11,0:03:52.10,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
